        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 28 at 12:18AM CDT until June 28 at 12:45AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1218 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles east of
Linton, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of east
central Emmons County.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for south central
and southeastern North Dakota.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
